com.kuka.capabilities

Interface ICapabilityContainer

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IExtendedCapabilityContainer, IResourceConnector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CapabilitySupport, DelegatingCapabilitySupport, PhysicalObject, SerialKinematics, SpatialObject, Tool, VirtualObject, World

    public interface ICapabilityContainer
    Implemented by classes that support capabilities, i.e. additional interfaces associated by aggregation and attachable at runtime. Once attached, a capability can't be detached or replaced.
    See Also:
    IExtendedCapabilityContainer

    • Method Detail

      • getCapability

        <T> T getCapability(Class<T> clazz)
        Gets a specific capability.

        Note: Only exact matching of capability types is supported. Inheritance hierarchy is not considered.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the requested capability for static type safety.
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class of the capability to get.
        Returns:
        The capability, never null. Once a capability has been returned, subsequent calls to getCapability(Class) always return the same capability object for the same Class.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if clazz is null
        CapabilityNotAvailableException - if no capability has been associated with clazz.

      • hasCapability

        boolean hasCapability(Class<?> clazz)
        Checks whether a capability of the specified Class is available. This is useful to avoid the CapabilityNotAvailableException of the getCapability(Class) method.
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class of the capability to check.
        Returns:
        true if the requested capability is available, false otherwise. Once true has been returned, subsequent calls for the same Class always return true.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if clazz is null
